"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-27-aiming-olympic-success-troubled-world\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Mr Bob Marley's 1979 classic So Much Trouble in the World pretty much sums up human existence in every age.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"score\": 0.6936984665499167, \"rank\": 0.4408747700380835, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So we are not surprised that, even as organisers made last-minute preparations for Friday's colourful, official launch of the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, an attack by saboteurs caused serious disruptions.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9223839143945943, \"rank\": 0.07539960387652936, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"News reports say arson and vandalism targeting France's high speed rail network led to travel chaos across the country.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 373, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9223839143945943, \"rank\": 0.07539960387652936, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully, the opening ceremony in Paris, featuring thousands of athletes parading by boat down the Seine, went well from all accounts.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 483, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.7234280471605744e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was unclear up to late Friday as to what motivated the saboteurs.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there is no shortage of fanatics with causes; be they part of mainstream or fringe movements.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, yesterday's attack on the French rail network triggered thoughts of the potential for much, much worse.\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 792, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.8826496169717803, \"rank\": 0.08764463062745095, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inevitably, memories were cast back to the so-called Munich Massacre at the 1972 Olympics in Munich, Germany.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_massacre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Munich Massacre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_massacre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_massacre\"}, {\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6618146472361857, \"rank\": 0.5105448354504096, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9988125010581768, \"rank\": 0.001187257142022709, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then armed terrorists from the Black September Movement, a so-called splinter of the Palestinian Liberation Organisation (PLO), ended up killing 11 Israeli athletes and coaches following a failed kidnapping attempt and botched rescue mission.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1018, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_September_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9999999972774276, \"rank\": 2.72274402304349e-09, \"text\": \"Black September\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_September_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_September_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Palestinian Liberation Organisation\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3384292353141053e-26, \"text\": \"PLO\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 0.999876896964797, \"rank\": 9.085309526568644e-05, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others, including a policeman and several Palestinian gunmen, also died.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_fedayeen\", \"score\": 0.8954785222641312, \"rank\": 0.11641305065512854, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_fedayeen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_fedayeen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In today's world, political instability, wars, and rumours of war, are casting long shadows just as was the case back in 1972.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us consider that Russia's invasion of Ukraine, in breach of international law and the Olympic Charter, has led to their exclusion from the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9994359469136239, \"rank\": 0.0005565396227119912, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1475, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9995741835308278, \"rank\": 0.00042073479852290023, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And while Israel is well represented at these Olympics, there is strong opposition led by Iran because of alleged genocide by the Israeli army against civilians in Gaza.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.14247236907844e-16, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 1720, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Israeli army\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 1754, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9972878419087828, \"rank\": 0.002719533897243368, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For those unaware, the troubles in Gaza are a continuation of hostilities involving Israel and Palestinians dating back nearly eight decades - embracing the Munich tragedy of 1972.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9972878419087828, \"rank\": 0.002719533897243368, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.14247236907844e-16, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 1856, \"end\": 1868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9998904283627957, \"rank\": 6.547030052091136e-05, \"text\": \"Palestinians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 1918, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6618146472361857, \"rank\": 0.5105448354504096, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today we are comforted by the near-unprecedented level of security in place in Paris and wider France to protect thousands of competitors and support staff from 205 international delegations and their supporters.\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2022, \"end\": 2027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9223839143945943, \"rank\": 0.07539960387652936, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"News reports say that ahead of Friday's ceremony, 45,000 police, more than 10,000 soldiers, alongside other specialised units, manned the centre of Paris.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In excess of 1,000 police personnel were said to have been on duty in and around the stadium as Israel and Mali played to a 1-1 draw in Olympic football on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2409, \"end\": 2415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.14247236907844e-16, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_War\", \"score\": 0.9822415936482514, \"rank\": 0.018079468841816635, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_War\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such high levels of security, and the clear determination by the French to ensure safety, trigger optimism, despite Friday morning's attack on rail services.\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2546, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.8826496169717803, \"rank\": 0.08764463062745095, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will help competitors - regardless of nationality or sporting discipline - to focus on performance without undue distraction by anyone or anything.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All should be following the example of Jamaica's 400-metre medal hopeful, Miss Nickisha Pryce.\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Said she, as told to us by our reporter in Paris: \\\"There is no pressure on me going into the Olympics, because I am just doing me\\u2026\\\"  That's as it should be.\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 3044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2931, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as we dream of excellence from Jamaica's ambassadors in Paris, we hope for all that's good for these Games, the Olympic movement, and sport as a whole.\", \"from\": 3046, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3082, \"end\": 3089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999997157039564, \"rank\": 2.8332903647991017e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 3107, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9162174463713933e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": []}]}"